The paper is about fraud detection on electronic payment platforms, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a novel fraud detection model that uses machine learning techniques, such as Adversarial Autoencoder (AAE), to analyze user behaviors and detect fraud. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of fraud detection in practice, which involves data analysis and processing, making it relevant to the category of cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper proposes a real-world data-oriented detection paradigm, which involves designing and implementing a system, making it relevant to the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
